{
  "texts": [
    "We identified 17 articles that involved users who were also primary stakeholders and one that involved a non-user who was also the primary stakeholder (Table 5 and \"Appendix 2\").We categorised the AI-enabled systems or POCs used or described in the 45 included articles into phases of AI If the included articles did not mention primary stakeholders, we made assumptions about who the primary stakeholders would be in their use cases Harm preventionConducting an initial evaluation Our review findings suggested to start with an evaluation whether the use of AIenabled systems for a specific use case or setting was useful, appropriate, and unlikely to lead to any obvious potential harm [33].",
    "If evaluation results were unfavourable, the findings suggested against using the AI-enabled system.",
    "For example, one study analysed an emotion AI-enabled system used in hiring services.",
    "The analysis revealed that the system displayed bias in facial emotion recognition across racial, gender, and disability characteristics.",
    "This bias prevented job applicants from effectively expressing their emotional qualities during recruitment, benefiting hiring organisations while disadvantaging candidates [34]."
  ]
}